h2. Spec::Rails - Installation - Quick Start

h4. Install

We strongly recommend you install RSpec and Spec::Rails as plugins (as opposed to relying on an RSpec gem).
See special instructions below if you want to install the HEAD of the trunk, or an older version.

h4. Installing the CURRENT release

Each release is mirrored in tags/CURRENT, so you can simply point at this to get the latest release.

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/CURRENT/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/CURRENT/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

If you're using svn for your project, install with -x.

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/CURRENT/rspec
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/CURRENT/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h4. Installing a specific release

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/{svn_tag: }/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/{svn_tag: }/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

... or (using svn externals) ...

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/{svn_tag: }/rspec
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/{svn_tag: }/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h4. Bootstrap

Once the plugin is installed, you must bootstrap your Rails app with RSpec. Stand in the root of your Rails app and run:

<pre>
ruby script/generate rspec
</pre>

This will generate the various files needed to use RSpec with Rails.

h4. Run specs with rake ...

<pre>
rake spec
</pre>

h4. ... or run specs with scripts/spec

<pre>
ruby script/spec spec
</pre>

h2. Living on the Edge

If you prefer to live dangerously you can get the HEAD of the trunk instead of installing from a tag.

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

If your own project is in Subversion and you'd like Spec::Rails to always follow HEAD, install with -x:

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h2. Releases 0.7.5 to 0.9.x (not really recommended at this point)

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec_on_rails/vendor/plugins/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h2. Releases < 0.7.5 (really not recommended at this point)

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/vendor/rspec_on_rails/vendor/plugins/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

